# OSS distribution setup <!--lmd:a summary-->

This session prepared Linked Markdown for open-source distribution: it rewrote the
project docs, wired up a hosted demo, packaged a Claude plugin, added ChatGPT and
Gemini authoring configs, and stubbed a release pipeline. It builds on
<!--lmd:ref source=guide:intro-->the format's getting-started guide<!--/lmd-->.

This note itself was produced by the plugin's `/lmd-capture` command — an example of
turning a working session into a linked note.

## Decisions <!--lmd:a decisions-->

- The GitHub Pages site hosts the docs at the root and the interactive playground at
  `/play`; deployment stays manual until explicitly enabled.
- The Claude plugin is **file-based** (no background server): it authors and links
  `.lmd` files and reads the graph through the `lmd` CLI. This scope was chosen to
  keep <!--lmd:ref impacts=:plan-->the first version<!--/lmd--> small.
- ChatGPT and Gemini get instructions-based configs; the GPT Store and Gemini Gems
  have no publish API, so they are submitted by hand.

## Plan and next steps <!--lmd:a plan-->

- Enable GitHub Pages (Settings → Pages → GitHub Actions) and run the Pages workflow.
- Replace the demo mockups with a real recorded GIF once the demo is hosted.
- Add registry tokens to activate the guarded release channels (npm, crates.io,
  VS Code Marketplace, Open VSX).

## Files touched <!--lmd:a touched-->

- `README.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, `CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md` — rewritten or updated.
- `.github/workflows/pages.yml`, `.github/workflows/release.yml`,
  `.github/scripts/validate-plugin.mjs`.
- `plugins/linked-markdown/` — the Claude plugin (skill, commands, session hook).
- `integrations/` — the provider-neutral, ChatGPT, and Gemini authoring configs.

